{
  "stem": "12447.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At one time, I had an arrangements with my father that I would get on a streetcar that was running through the ghetto, and my father would wait at one point.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the back-- you know, like a streetcar, was-- on one side was a policeman with the steps which you walked up.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The tramway, the streetcar, came to the ghetto stop to the gate.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was a policeman that got on, on the tramway, on the streetcar.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And nobody was able to get off in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the tram, or the streetcar, was going through the ghetto because they couldn't cut off the line.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they let the tramway, the streetcar, cut-- travel through the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then at the other end, the policeman would get off.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And people continued.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "All the passengers were Polish passengers that were just crossing the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So what I would do, I'd get on the tram-- on this streetcar-- and I had a little bag arranged sometimes with some cereal in that bag.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Sometimes was a, a small bread inside, as much as I could-- I could carry.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the back of the-- where the policeman was, the streetcar was built in a way that you could open it in both ways.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But sometimes, they only had it open on one side, and it was like an iron gate-- and the back of the streetcar from the opposite side where the policeman would get off.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So the gate had like big openings, like maybe, I don't know, a foot wide or something.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I remember when I made up with my father, that they would wait for me, I'd push a package through that opening.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my father would catch it on the other side.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
